Expression matrices

Read in expression matrices and filter expression matrices to only contain cohort and samples of interest using histology file

exp_file <- file.path(data_dir,"gene-expression-rsem-tpm-collapsed.rds")
expressionMatrix<-readRDS(exp_file) 

clinical_filtered <- clinical %>% dplyr::filter(sample_type == "Tumor") %>%
  dplyr::filter(experimental_strategy == "RNA-Seq") %>% 
  dplyr::filter(cohort %in% c("PBTA", "GMKF", "TARGET")) 

# filter to samples of a particular RNA library type
polya_samples <- clinical_filtered %>% dplyr::filter(RNA_library == "poly-A") %>%
  dplyr::pull(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID)
stranded_samples <- clinical_filtered %>% dplyr::filter(RNA_library == "stranded") %>%
  dplyr::pull(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID)
polya_stranded_samples <- clinical_filtered %>% dplyr::filter(RNA_library == "poly-A stranded") %>%
  dplyr::pull(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID)

# seperate exptression matrix to sample of interest 
expressionMatrix_polyA <- expressionMatrix %>% dplyr::select(polya_samples) %>%
  rownames_to_column()

expressionMatrix_stranded <- expressionMatrix %>% dplyr::select(stranded_samples) %>%
  rownames_to_column()

expressionMatrix_polyA_stranded <- expressionMatrix %>% dplyr::select(polya_stranded_samples) %>%
  rownames_to_column()

Format expression matrices to long format

expression_mat_to_long <- function(expressionMatrix,score_df,gene){
# use filtered expression matrix for expression based filtering for less than given threshold
# Taking snippet from @jaclyn-taroni idea used in expression based fusion call filtering

expression_long_df <- expressionMatrix %>%
  # rename rowname to GeneSymbol
  dplyr::rename(GeneSymbol=rowname) %>%
  # filter to gene of interest
  dplyr::filter(GeneSymbol == gene) %>%
  # Get the data into long format
  reshape2::melt(variable.name = "Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID",
                 value.name = "expression_value") %>%
  dplyr::mutate(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID= as.character(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID)) 

# merge score and expression file
merge_score_exp <- expression_long_df %>%
  left_join(score_df, by=c("Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID"="sample_id"))

return(merge_score_exp)
}

polya_exp_score <- expression_mat_to_long(expressionMatrix_polyA,score_df,"TP53")
Using GeneSymbol as id variables
stranded_exp_score <- expression_mat_to_long(expressionMatrix_stranded,score_df,"TP53")
Using GeneSymbol as id variables
polya_stranded_exp_score <- expression_mat_to_long(expressionMatrix_polyA_stranded,score_df,"TP53")

stranded TP53 expression to classifier_score has a negative correlation estimate -0.21 at p value 9.816063e-17

polya TP53 expression to classifier_score has a negligible negative correlation estimate -0.095 at p value 0.1330592

polya stranded TP53 expression to classifier_score has a negative correlation estimate -0.326 at p value 5.642812e-20

Overall distribution of expression and classifier score shows negative correlation. For stranded and polya stranded, there are statistically significant negative correlation of -0.21 and -0.326. For these two methods. it seemed like expression/classifier score is correlated with functionality/ phenotype of TP53 inactivation in samples. For polyA samples, there is a negative correlation estimate of -0.095 at p value 0.1330592. And we cannot directly use the expression/classifier score to infer functionality/phenotype of TP53 inactivation in samples
